      "content": "Here's a Python script that should do the trick:\n```python\nimport os\nimport shutil\n\n# Define the directory to clean up\ndir_to_cleanup = '/var/lib/llama-agent/configs/'\n\n# Remove all config files\nfor filename in os.listdir(dir_to_cleanup):\n    if filename.endswith('.config'):\n        file_path = os.path.join(dir_to_cleanup, filename)\n        os.remove(file_path)\n        print(f\"Removed config file: {filename}\")\n\n# Remove all log files\nfor root, dirs, files in os.walk(dir_to_cleanup, topdown=False):\n    for file in files:\n        if file.endswith('.log'):\n            file_path = os.path.join(root, file)\n            os.remove(file_path)\n            print(f\"Removed log file: {file}\")\n\n# Print a success message\nprint(f\"Cleanup complete. {dir_to_cleanup} is now empty.\")\n```\nPlease note that you'll need to run this script with root privileges to access the directory.",
